rComments: A very friendly, brilliant professor. However, the coursework was fairly challenging for a second year course, if extremely enjoyable. She knew where she was starting each lecture, but the constant discussion sometimes led into tangents - however overall, it was a great experience.

Her lectures either had no relation to the material or just summarized it. She generally spoke straight nonsense while making funny hand motions and drawing meaningless diagrams on the board. Easy grade and entertaining to watch, but by the end of the year it gets old.

Knott may appear as if she just walked in off the street, but don't let that undermine your ideas of what a great teacher she is. Very committed, extremely inquisitive, and has an uncanny ability to translate even the most esoteric of ideas into language even a 2 year old could understand. Great, great prof!

Knott is an excellent thinker. She is obviously very committed to the class, and *really* exploring the ideas and texts. The course would be difficult for anybody ESL (espec. the readings), but definitely worthwhile for everyone. One of those courses where it really is as good as you make it.
I agree about her making difficult concepts easy to grasp. A great prof.!
An unusually good teacher, made even difficult ideas very accessible
